column5: Nice fishin DAWG !!!!!    looks like a great fish-fry in the works bud,nice colors,on those big bull gills too !!!!...cheers buddy
Nice little fishies there G.  Joey
great report.  mild temps meaning like 95? lol  cheers!
So the nudity starts promptly at noon?  Great report as usual Glen....you on a diet?
Nice report GCD!  A mess 'o fish you got yerself!  Amazing they were biting in that soup.  Good job.

Great report Glen! Looks like a busy morning with the fish. Nice to have the lake to yourself also. I noticed in the cat pics that you're holding them in your BARE hands. That's not very prudent is it?  Some members here hold them with a Boga or even welder's mitts because of the possibility of sustaining a lethal injection of fish slime. I guess you must be used to holding them. Or maybe the blue catfish don't have shooting darts or death rays for eyes or those 32 volt whiskers??
Sure they weren't stunned or "shocked and awed" by your nudity?   That's a lot of food. Where's your big belly?  Good job redder nek!
Great Report! As usual lots of species to target. I'm just surprised that you have a lake all to yourself in the States!
Wow...that is some warm water!  nice job, GCD
Isn't there a saying about..  "Mad Dawgs and Englishmen go out in the midday sun"  Just kiddin' Dawg...Nice catch !!!

Great report and pics Glen!  When I first started reading and I saw you were wearing your shirt, I thought that it couldn't be that cold down there, since we are roasting in 90F heat up here.  Then the later pictures showed the Glen we all know....LOL.  Very interesting seeing the water temps rise like that during the day....it was almost a steam bath in that last pic there!  Oh yeah...nice fish...that catfish looking at the date was hilarious!!!
Nice pictures and fish Glen.  Looks like it was a lovely Alabama day!!  about picture #13...could use a wee bit of editing  lol
Great report Glenn.  It was going so well, I was sitting here reading, and then BAM! the shirt came off. Did you have to?
LOL Roy your killin me Roy thanks for the Laugh neighbor  Excellent report Glen .Have you been working out again
Very nice, some good size fish there! Keep it up,looking forward to more reports! -Little Angler
Some good action and haul, WTG...
Sucking in your tummy eh....a little bit of love handle happening on the right side  hahaha Great report and pics
that spot never fails you eh! and it seems that you get a mixed bag of stuff everytime you go there.  Nice report Glen ... no mouthwatering fishfry pic?
Great report and pics Glen....geez..that lake water temp is warmer then my bath water

nice fish GCD  those bull gills and large strawberry bass can put up a nice fight on light tackle.  that surface temp was really warm..  did u manage to find those fish a little deeper or in some heavy cover?
Great report as usual GCD. I never knew catfish were that evil...what with all the voltage and death slime shooting darts....lol.
You sure showed them who's boss Must of been a blast fighting bass on light tackle  God job GCD and thanks for sharing Leechman
That's not a love handle.
